4 FOR
HOUSE BILL NO. 3787 By: Chapman
5
6
7 PROPOSED POLICY COMMITTEE SUBSTITUTE
8 An Act relating to elections; prohibiting persons who
are not a qualified elector from filing as a
9 candidate for any municipal office; prohibiting non-
qualified electors from being appointed to any
10 municipal office; amending 26 O.S. 2021, Section 5-
105, as amended by Section 1, Chapter 43, O.S.L. 2022
11 (26 O.S. Supp. 2025, Section 5-105), which relates to
registration requirements for candidates for state or
12 county office; requiring candidates to be qualified
electors; prohibiting nonqualified electors from
13 being elected to or serving on a board of education
for a school district or technology center school
14 district; providing for codification; and providing
an effective date.
15
16
17 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
18 SECTION 1. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
19 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 16-115 of Title 11, unless there
20 is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
21 No person who is not a qualified elector as described in Section
22 1 of Article III of the Oklahoma Constitution may file as a
23 candidate for any municipal office. Such persons shall also be
24 prohibited from appointment to any municipal office.
Req. No. 16292 Page 1

1 SECTION 2. AMENDATORY 26 O.S. 2021, Section 5-105, as
2 amended by Section 1, Chapter 43, O.S.L. 2022 (26 O.S. Supp. 2025,
3 Section 5-105), is amended to read as follows:
4 Section 5-105. A. To file as a candidate for nomination by a
5 political party to any state or county office, a person must have
6 been a registered voter of that party for the six-month period
7 immediately preceding the first day of the filing period prescribed
8 by law and, under oath, so state. Provided, this requirement shall
9 not apply to a candidate for the nomination of a political party
10 which attains recognition less than six (6) months preceding the
11 first day of the filing period required by law. However, the
12 candidate shall be required to have registered with the newly
13 recognized party within fifteen (15) days after such party
14 recognition.
15 B. To file as an independent candidate for any state or county
16 office, a person must have been registered to vote as an independent
17 for the six-month period immediately preceding the first day of the
18 filing period prescribed by law and, under oath, so state.
19 C. To file as a candidate under either subsection A or B of
20 this section, a candidate must be a qualified elector as described
21 in Section 1 of Article III of the Oklahoma Constitution.
22 SECTION 3. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
23 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 13A-112 of Title 26, unless
24 there is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
Req. No. 16292 Page 2

1 No person may be elected to, or serve on, a board of education
2 of a school district or technology center school district who is not
3 a qualified elector as described in Section 1 of Article III of the
4 Oklahoma Constitution.
5 SECTION 4. This act shall become effective November 1, 2026.
